Class ConfigurableLogicalFormulaCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.util.StringTools
      • org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers.FormulaCompiler
        • org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers.FormulaCompilerLibSBML
          • org.sbml.jsbml.util.compilers.ConfigurableLogicalFormulaCompiler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ASTNodeCompiler

    public class ConfigurableLogicalFormulaCompiler
extends FormulaCompilerLibSBML
    This class creates formula Strings that represent the content of ASTNodes and try to reproduce an output similar to old COBRA SBML files.

    "and" and "or" are configurable. This is the only difference between this compiler and the FormulaCompilerLibSBML.

    Since:
    1.4
    Author:
    Thomas Hamm, Nicolas Rodriguez

        public void setAndReplacement​(java.lang.String andReplacement)
        Sets the String that will be used to replace ' and ' (the mathML <and> element) in the boolean expressions. The default value used is ' & '. If null is given, no replacement will be performed.
